# TKR - Project Task Management

## Instructions

You are working with the tkr task management system. Tickets are stored as
Markdown files with YAML frontmatter in `.tkr/tickets/`.

**Workflow:**
1. Run `tkr next --plain` to get your next assigned task
2. Run `tkr claim <id>` to mark it as in-progress
3. Complete the work described in the ticket
4. Run `tkr done <id>` when finished

**Rules:**
- NEVER create tasks with `TaskCreate` -- use `tkr new` instead
- ALWAYS check `tkr next --plain` before starting work
- ALWAYS include the ticket ID in your commit messages: `feat({{.Prefix}}-N): description`
- Read the full ticket with `tkr show <id> --plain` before starting work
- Verify acceptance criteria with the ticket before marking done

**Commands:**
- `tkr next --plain` -- Get the next available task
- `tkr show <id> --plain` -- Show full task details
- `tkr claim <id>` -- Start working on a task
- `tkr done <id>` -- Mark a task as complete
- `tkr list --plain` -- List all tasks
- `tkr lint` -- Validate all tickets
